      • indexOf

        public int[] indexOf(Character el,
                     int size)
        Description copied from class: LookupList
        Find at most size indexes i where 
        
   this.get(i).equals(el)

        The return value is in natural order.

        This method could be used to find duplicates in the list as follows:

        
   public  E findDuplicate(LookupList list) {
     for (E el: list) {
       if (list.indexOf(el, 2).length == 2) {
         return el;
       }
     }
     return null;
   }
        If size < 0, all indexes of el are returned. If el is not in the list, this returns an empty array.
        Specified by:
        indexOf in class LookupList<Character>
        Parameters:
        el - an object
        size - a number
        Returns:
        an array of length size or less, or an array of all indexes of el if size < 0

      • group

        public Map<Character,int[]> group()
        Description copied from class: LookupList
        Group the elements in this list. This returns a map where each distinct value in the list is mapped to an array of all the indexes where it appears. This array of indexes is in ascending order.
